<p>Overall, these S&T enablers performed well and provided the future force with tangible and important combat capabilities.  Some, such as the Cargo UAS (see image 1) provided the Army with the ability to examine nascent existing capabilities and determine best concepts for employment to increase sustainment efficiency.  Others, such as the Army High Energy Laser (HEL) Mobile Demonstrator (see image 2), provided increased protection against enemy rockets, mortars, missiles and unmanned aerial vehicles.  The requirements to maintain and utilize these enablers at BCT level and below potentially increases the physical and cognitive demands on Soldiers, but these additional demands did not outweigh the benefits and overmatch capabilities of these emerging technologies.<span class="endnoteRef">[5]</span></p>
<div class="blockCallout" id="alignRt">
			<div class="blocktitle" id="cap320">Image 2</div>
			<div class="blockimage"><asp:HyperLink runat="server"
